As for the socio-demographic variables, overall we found that differences on stress emerged only according to gender and having or not children. Indeed, females showed higher levels of distress than males. This result was in line with previous literature on the theme (
 Matud, 2004; 
 West, Dyrbye, and Shanafelt, 2018; 
 Hirsch et al., 2020), with a recent study carried out on Italian general population during the current COVID-19 outbreak (
 Flesia et al., 2020) and also with the normative data collected in Italy (
 Mondo, Sechi, and Cabras, 2019).
